cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for learning word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the representation of knowledge in machine learning models. "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as word embeddings are often used in information retrieval tasks. Finally, "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as word embeddings are often used in network analysis.
